{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-15T10:00:00Z", "url": "https://physics.aps.org/articles/v18/s49", "publishedAt": "2025-04-15T10:00:00Z", "content": "The preferred tool for imaging cells is the optical microscope, as it has the resolution needed to capture a cell’s main components. The technique works well if the cells only need to be observed for… [+2197 chars]", "title": "AI Gives Ultrasound Imaging a Boost", "fullContent": "Synopsis\n\nAI Gives Ultrasound Imaging a Boost\n\nA new method for obtaining high-resolution images of cells from low-resolution ultrasound data enables longer, noninvasive monitoring of organisms.\n\nThe preferred tool for imaging cells is the optical microscope, as it has the resolution needed to capture a cell’s main components. The technique works well if the cells only need to be observed for a few hours, but it breaks down for longer times, as photons from the light source eventually damage the cells. Ultrasound imaging allows for longer viewing times—24 hours or more—but its long wavelength, which can’t be shorter than a few hundred micrometers, leads to a resolution that is typically too low to be useful. Now Hirotsugu Ogi of the University of Osaka, Japan, and colleagues have demonstrated an artificial-intelligence (AI)-based method that can give low-resolution images of cells a high-resolution makeover [1]. Ogi expects that their method could improve the resolution of other types of microscopes.\n\nFor their demonstration the researchers collected more than 100,000 ultrasound and optical images of the same live stem cells. The images were then fed into an AI algorithm, which was trained to learn the relationship between the features of the two sets of images. The team then tested the algorithm with a new set of ultrasound images of cells and found that the output images matched the optical images of those cells. Ogi says that the key to the success was including both low- and high-frequency acoustic signals in the images. The low-frequency data capture mechanical resonances of the cell nucleus, which turned out to be needed to train the AI algorithm correctly.\n\n–Katherine Wright\n\nKatherine Wright is the Deputy Editor of Physics Magazine.\n\nReferences et al., “Deep-learning generation of high-resolution images of live cells in culture using tri-frequency acoustic images,” N. Fujiwara, “Deep-learning generation of high-resolution images of live cells in culture using tri-frequency acoustic images,” Phys. Rev. X 15, 021015 (2025)"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-15T15:00:13Z", "url": "https://www.wpbeginner.com/news/welcome-athemes-to-the-wpbeginner-family-of-products/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-15T15:00:13Z", "content": "Today, Im extremely excited to share that aThemes is joining the Awesome Motive network, and theyre now part of the WPBeginner family of products.\r\naThemes is a popular WordPress theme company known … [+5639 chars]", "title": "Welcome aThemes to the WPBeginner Family of Products", "fullContent": "Today, I’m extremely excited to share that aThemes is joining the Awesome Motive network, and they’re now part of the WPBeginner family of products.\n\naThemes is a popular WordPress theme company known for building beautiful website templates that are optimized for speed and performance. Over 130,000+ websites use aThemes’ WordPress themes and plugins to build an online presence, launch online stores, and grow revenue.\n\nIntroduction to aThemes – Quick Overview\n\naThemes offers professionally designed WordPress themes to help you quickly get your business online.\n\nThey are the company behind two popular WordPress themes, Sydney and Botiga. Both of them are rated 4.9 out of 5 on WordPress.org with an impressive 850+ 5-star reviews.\n\nLet’s take a detailed look.\n\nSydney is a great all-purpose free WordPress theme, used by over 100,000 websites. It offers tons of professionally designed starter site templates to help you quickly launch your website.\n\nAll you have to do is import a starter site and start customizing your website the way you want.\n\nOne of the best things about the Sydney theme is that it comes with an easy-to-use template builder, which transforms the way you build a website.\n\nFor example, you can replace theme-built components like header, footer, etc., on specific pages or everywhere.\n\nYou can also use the global template to create parts for all pages. Alternatively, you can create multiple templates and assign them to specific pages.\n\nTake a look at some other cool features of Sydney:\n\nCreate a highly customized header by choosing from 8 different header presets.\n\nQuickly customize your blog layout with its easy-to-use layout presets and flexible controls.\n\nEasily select a preset color palette that matches your brand. Or you can create your own from scratch.\n\nAdd as many sidebars as you want and control the display with conditions.\n\nAnd more…\n\nFeel free to download the free version of Sydney from WordPress.org.\n\nBotiga is a lightweight WooCommerce theme that is designed for optimal performance while boosting conversions.\n\nIt lets you easily showcase your eCommerce products and customize every part of your online store in real time. You can customize your product pages, checkout pages, and more.\n\nEasily Customize Your Product Pages\n\nOut of the box, it comes with three gallery styles for your product page to showcase your products.\n\nIt allows you to edit every aspect of your product card style, tweak the card layouts, and position add-to-cart buttons the way you want.\n\nYou can even create a fly-out mini cart to show cart details at a glance without interrupting your customers’ browsing experience.\n\nBoost Conversions on Your Checkout Pages\n\nDo you want to optimize your checkout page to boost conversions?\n\nBotiga allows you to display the total amount of the products on the right side or at the bottom of your cart and checkout pages.\n\nThat way, your customers can quickly review their order and find all relevant information easily.\n\nFeel free to download the free version of Botiga from WordPress.org.\n\nOther aThemes Products\n\nAside from WordPress themes, aThemes also offers two different WordPress plugins. They are:\n\naThemes Merchant\n\naThemes Merchant is an all-in-one WooCommerce growth tool that lets you increase revenue, retain customers, and boost AOV.\n\nWith Merchant, you can offer product bundles, frequently bought together products, bulk discounts, free gifts, and more.\n\naThemes Addons for Elementor\n\naThemes Addons brings together all the essential Elementor widgets you’ll need to create perfect websites.\n\nIt offers 55+ widgets, which can help you transform your Elementor workflow.\n\nBackground Story – Why aThemes?\n\nIn our annual WPBeginner reader survey, one of the user suggestions that we always get is to build a FREE WordPress theme that makes it easy to create stunning websites.\n\nNow, as you know, my focus has entirely been on building our WordPress plugins and software products, which are now used by over 30 million websites (thanks to your support). But I simply couldn’t ignore this request from the WPBeginner community.\n\nWhile we offer ThriveThemes (a premium suite of theme builder and WordPress growth plugins) and SeedProd AI theme builder (a premium tool that creates a site in seconds), we didn’t have a good free WordPress theme option.\n\nSo I started talking to some of my friends, and then Charlie Livingston, the founder of aThemes, reached out about potentially looking to exit the business. After a few short conversations, we signed the deal because it aligned with both of our visions.\n\nCharlie wanted the business to go in the hands of someone reputable and who has a proven track record of building great products.\n\nI knew our readers wanted us to build a free theme, and we had already been recommending the Sydney theme in our various articles because it’s a very high-quality theme.\n\nWhat’s Coming Next?\n\nOur work is just starting.\n\nMy goal is to create the best WordPress themes on the market while keeping them affordable and accessible to everyone. We have an exciting roadmap ahead that focuses on bringing premium-quality designs at a price point that makes sense for small business owners.\n\nIf you have suggestions on features you’d like to see in future theme releases, then please let us know by sending us a message via the WPBeginner contact form.\n\nAs always, I want to thank you for your continued support of WPBeginner.\n\nEvery time I share an announcement like this, I realize that I’m only able to do what I love every day because of you, our amazing readers, and I’m extremely grateful for your support throughout the years.\n\nWPBeginner and Awesome Motive would not be here without YOU, and I just want to say how much I appreciate all of you.\n\nAnd I look forward to continuing serving you, and the larger WordPress / web ecosystem for years to come.\n\nYours Truly,\n\nSyed Balkhi\n\nFounder of WPBeginner"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-15T23:00:00Z", "url": "https://anfieldindex.com/80984/liverpool-2-1-west-ham-united-final-thoughts-as-reds-edge-closer-to-20th-premier-league-title.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-15T23:00:00Z", "content": "After a frustrating 3-2 loss away to Fulham the previous weekend, Liverpool returned to Anfield with both a point to prove and an opportunity to take a significant step toward the Premier League titl… [+4414 chars]", "title": "Liverpool 2-1 West Ham United: Final Thoughts as Reds Edge Closer to 20th League Title", "fullContent": "Liverpool 2 – 1 West Ham United – The Postmortem\n\nAfter a frustrating 3-2 loss away to Fulham the previous weekend, Liverpool returned to Anfield with both a point to prove and an opportunity to take a significant step toward the Premier League title. Arsenal’s 1-1 home draw with Brentford meant that just nine points from their final seven fixtures would be enough to secure a historic 20th league championship.\n\nWest Ham arrived intent on frustrating the Reds and hitting on the counter. It was a strategy that caused discomfort at times, but Arne Slot’s men showed composure, resilience, and just enough cutting edge to grind out a critical victory.\n\nBelow is how the team lined up, with match details following.\n\nhttps://twitter.com/anfieldindex/status/1911726122636620075?s=46&t=rxgukmqdoXc4muVFLSx2EQ\n\nThe Starting Eleven\n\nGK – Alisson Becker\n\nRB – Conor Bradley\n\nRCB – Ibrahima Konaté\n\nLCB – Virgil van Dijk (c)\n\nLB – Kostas Tsimikas\n\nCM – Alexis Mac Allister\n\nACM – Curtis Jones\n\nCM – Ryan Gravenberch\n\nRF – Mohamed Salah\n\nCF – Diogo Jota\n\nLF – Luis Díaz\n\nSubs:\n\nAndy Robertson – Kostas Tsimikas (60 mins)\n\nCody Gakpo – Diogo Jota (60 mins)\n\nDominik Szoboszlai – Curtis Jones (68 mins)\n\nJarell Quansah – Conor Bradley (68 mins)\n\nWataru Endō – Mohamed Salah (84 min)\n\nGoals (Assisted by)\n\nLiverpool 1 – 0 West Ham\n\nLuis Díaz (Mohamed Salah) – 18 mins\n\nLiverpool 1 – 1 West Ham\n\nOwn Goal (Andy Robertson) – 66 mins\n\nLiverpool 2 – 1 West Ham\n\nVirgil van Dijk (Andy Robertson) – 72 mins\n\n🟥 Player Ratings – Liverpool 2-1 West Ham: Reds Grind Out Win in Tight Title Race ✍️ @StevLFChttps://t.co/Ad6U8LGx30 — AnfieldIndex (@AnfieldIndex) April 13, 2025\n\nImportant Match Stats\n\nPossession\n\nLiverpool 55% – 45% West Ham\n\nXG\n\nLiverpool 1.78 – 2.48 West Ham\n\nTotal Shots\n\nLiverpool 15 – 11 West Ham\n\nCorner Kicks\n\nLiverpool 10 – 3 West Ham\n\nOffsides\n\nLiverpool 5 – 4 West Ham\n\nFouls\n\nLiverpool 15 – 8 West Ham\n\nYellow Cards\n\nLiverpool 0 – 2 West Ham\n\nGoalkeeper Saves\n\nLiverpool 4 – 4 West Ham\n\nThe First Half\n\nLiverpool started on the front foot, dominating possession and looking sharper than in their defeat at Craven Cottage. The midfield trio of Mac Allister, Gravenberch, and Jones dictated the tempo early on, while the returning Alisson provided a reassuring presence behind the backline.\n\nThe breakthrough came in the 18th minute. Mohamed Salah drifted inside from the right and slalomed past his marker before sliding a pass into Luis Díaz’s path. The Colombian forward timed his run perfectly and coolly slotted home to put Liverpool ahead.\n\nThough West Ham responded with a few dangerous moments on the break, Liverpool controlled the half, with Van Dijk and Konaté commanding in defence and Bradley offering energetic support from the right.\n\nIt would be later in the half that West Ham would start to offer more and more potency, which required Alisson Becker to make a super pair of saves to send his side into a fragile half-time lead.\n\nThe Second Half\n\nThe second half started with more balance, as West Ham grew in confidence and began to test Liverpool’s composure. Their persistence paid off in the 66th minute when Andy Robertson, trying to clear a dangerous cross shortly after coming on, inadvertently turned the ball into his net to level the game.\n\nIt was a setback—but one that drew a quick and decisive response. Just six minutes later, Robertson atoned for his error with a pinpoint corner that was met by the towering figure of Virgil van Dijk, who thundered home a header to restore Liverpool’s lead.\n\nSlot’s remaining substitutions did not manage the closing stages well and a late melee within the Liverpool box nearly saw the game drawn. West Ham pushed for another equaliser but were kept at bay by a relieved Liverpool side.\n\nFinal Thoughts\n\nThis was a gritty and important win. Not every performance can be dominant or fluid at this stage of a title race, and this one was about resilience as much as quality. Salah’s brilliance in the first half and Van Dijk’s leadership in the second proved the difference, alongside a ferocious performance of Alisson Becker.\n\nWhile West Ham made things difficult, Liverpool found the answers required and took another vital step toward lifting the Premier League trophy. With six games left, only two more wins are needed to make it official.\n\nNext up is a trip to Leicester City, where another massive three points will be the objective.\n\nSteven Smith’s Score Prediction:\n\nLiverpool 3 – 1 West Ham"}
